"n. 男修道院，僧院 【英】 n. 男修道院，僧院(a place of residence occupied by a community of monks, living in a religious seclusion) 【记】 mon(单个)+aster(星 星)→孤星→孤独者所 住之处→寺院 【例】 The orphan was taken to the local monastery. 无 【记】mono 单独 + sterile 不育的，一个人不育的→和尚；master 大师，能练出大师的地方→少林寺之类；man + ster 人→男人呆的地方 monastery (n.)  c.1400, from Old French monastere ""monastery"" (14c.) and directly from Late Latin monasterium, from Ecclesiastical Greek monasterion ""a monastery,"" from monazein ""to live alone,"" from monos ""alone"" (see mono-). With suffix -terion ""place for (doing something)."" Originally applied to houses of any religious order, male or female."
